<div>
<h2>For Your Information: Upcoming Changes to Domain Name Contact Data</h2>

<p>Hello,</p>

<p>Effective immediately, <strong>for gTLDs</strong> we are updating our do=
main name registration process to comply with <a href=3D"https://www.icann.=
org/en/contracted-parties/consensus-policies/registration-data-policy ">a n=
ew policy from ICANN</a> (Internet Corporation for Assigned Names and Numbe=
rs).</p>

<p>Here's a quick overview of what's changing:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>WHOIS Data:</strong> If your domain's registrant contact has =
an organization listed, that information will no longer be visible in the p=
ublic WHOIS/RDDS lookup, unless you have previously elected to display your=
 organization.</li>

  <li><strong>Contact Information We Collect:</strong> We will now only col=
lect the minimum contact data required by each registry. For most domains, =
this will only be the <strong>registrant contact</strong>. Some country cod=
e TLDs (ccTLDs) may still require administrative, billing, or technical con=
tacts.</li>

  <li><strong>Removal of Extra Data:</strong> Any contact information in ou=
r system that is no longer required by the registry will be deleted.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>You do not need to take any action.</strong> These changes will =
happen automatically</p>

</div>
